  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Facilitating the participation process of ethical trade formation in Thailand</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ethical trade such as Fair Trade has a potential to reduce inequalities but not yet established in Thailand.  Two networks are starting to discuss fair trade and becomes an opportunity for Oxfam Thailand to engage now.  Through the multi -stakeholder dialogue platform initiation, the project will define and design a fair trade  system, labeling and consumer movement to suit the Thailand context of an upper MIC with high inequalities.  Using the knowledge capital of Oxfam on Fairtrade and Fair Trade initiatives worldwide, the existing pilot model of fair trade on sustainable seafood of Oxfam Thailand, and the accumulating strength on urban consumer campaigning, Oxfam Thailand is in a unique position to influence the fair trade formation into social movement in Thailand to aim at high impact on the marginalized communities and women.</narrative>
  </description>
